    <div class="AssessmentProblem.type">ShortAnswerResponse</div>
    <div class="AssessmentProblem.statement"><p>Write two different sentences that use&#xA0;ratios to describe the number of eyes and legs in this picture.</p>

<div class="imgrid">
<div class="g--row g--row-1">
<div class="g--col-1 g--column g--content g--half g--row-1">
<p><img class="h-max-height--4-lines" src="/image_files/29465.png" /></p>
</div>

<div class="g--col-2 g--column g--content g--half g--row-1">
<p></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
    <div class="AssessmentProblem.solution"><p>Answers vary. Sample responses:</p>

<ul>
	<li>The ratio of legs to eyes is 8 to 4.</li>
	<li>The ratio of eyes to legs is <span class="math math-repaired" data-png-file-id="819">\(4:8\)</span>.</li>
	<li>There are 2 legs for every eye.</li>
	<li>There are 4 legs for every 2 eyes.</li>
</ul>
</div>
